original: 1.4 Method of Computing Expense Waiver . To determine the Expense Waiver (Investment Adviser ’s liability), each day the Fund Operating Expenses shall be  subtracted from the Fund Investment Income to produce the daily Net Investment Income. If the daily Net Investment Income is below zero for any day, the Investment Adviser shall first waive or reduce its advisory fee for such day by an amount  sufficient to bring the Net Investment Income to zero. If the amount of the waived or reduced advisory fee for any such day is insufficient to bring the Net Investment Income to zero , the Investment Adviser shall also pay Fund expenses or reimburse  the Fund an amount that, together with the waived or reduced advisory fee, is sufficient to bring the Net Investment Income to zero.

4. Miscellaneous Matters.

In the event that either Party (the "Party") fails to perform any obligation under this Agreement without delay or cause (the "Defaulting Party"), the non-defaulting Party reserves the right, but not the obligation, to suspend its own performance hereunder for a reasonable period of time to allow the Defaulting Party an opportunity to remedy such default. If the Defaulting Party fails to remedy such default within thirty (30) days following notice thereof, then the non-defaulting Party may terminate this Agreement with immediate effect and without liability.
